#: ../../user/troubleshooting/app-menu-shortcut-troubleshooting.rst:200
#: c378e3883cfc49a7ac27e8649a4fee25
msgid "Behind the scenes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/app-menu-shortcut-troubleshooting.rst:203
#: 234782f529e0471bb8f5af88c3255eb5
msgid ""
"``qvm-sync-appmenus`` works by invoking the *GetAppMenus* :doc:`Qubes "
"service </developer/services/qrexec>` in the target domain. This service "
"enumerates applications installed in that qube and sends formatted info back"
" to dom0 which creates ``.desktop`` files in the app qube/template directory"
" of dom0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/app-menu-shortcut-troubleshooting.rst:205
#: 8737a69614b04aedbfa884e9c6954a14
msgid ""
"For Linux qubes the service script is in :file:`/etc/qubes-"
"rpc/qubes.GetAppMenus``. In Windows it’s a PowerShell script located in "
":file:`c:\\Program Files\\Invisible Things Lab\\Qubes OS Windows "
"Tools\\qubes-rpc-services\\get-appmenus.ps1` by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/app-menu-shortcut-troubleshooting.rst:207
#: 805c8bd0b08c4466a1160466b4f8b758
msgid ""
"The list of installed applications for each app qube is stored in dom0’s "
":file:`~/.local/share/qubes-appmenus/{<QUBE_NAME>}/apps.templates`. Each "
"menu entry is a file that follows the `.desktop file format "
"<https://standards.freedesktop.org/desktop-entry-spec/desktop-entry-spec-"
"latest.html>`__ with some wildcards (``%VMNAME%``, ``%VMDIR%``). "
"Applications selected to appear in the menu are stored in "
":file:`~/.local/share/qubes-appmenus/{<QUBE_NAME>}/apps` and in "
":file:`~/.local/share/applications/`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/app-menu-shortcut-troubleshooting.rst:209
