msgid ""
"Note that you can create a shortcut that points to a ``.desktop`` file in "
"your app qube with e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/app-menu-shortcut-troubleshooting.rst:228
#: d5f46be3a65e4b60b8aabc9377e1dd47
msgid ""
"While this works well for standard applications, creating a menu entry for "
"Windows applications running under *wine* may need an additional step in "
"order to establish the necessary environment in *wine*. Installing software "
"under *wine* will create the needed ``.desktop`` file in the target Linux "
"qube in the directory :file:`~/.local/share/applications/wine/Programs/` or "
"a subdirectory thereof, depending on the Windows menu structure seen under "
"*wine*. If the name of this file contains spaces, it will not be found, "
"because the ``qvm-run`` command is falsely seen as terminating at this "
"space. The solution is to remove these spaces by renaming the ``.desktop`` "
"file accordingly, e.g. by renaming :file:`Microsoft Excel.desktop` to "
":file:`Excel.desktop`. Refreshing the menu structure will then build working"
" menu entries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/app-menu-shortcut-troubleshooting.rst:230
#: d3b15756dcb149d38ebc2e4fa26cfa03
msgid ""
"Applications installed under *wine* are installed in AppVMs, not in the "
"template on which these AppVMs are based, as the file structure used by "
"*wine* is stored under :file:`~/.wine`, which is part of the persistent data"
" of the AppVM and not inherited from its template."
msgstr ""
